<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="584" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,356,1352]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,520,500,525]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">
Male 
<typeStatus box="[268,371,500,525]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">holotype</typeStatus>
description.
</emphasis>
Length of forewing: 16.0 mm. Eye hairy. Antennal club with pale patch at base. Both wings same shaped as in 
<emphasis box="[494,575,536,560]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">P. l am a</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,356,1352]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">
Wing-pattern (
<figureCitation box="[365,452,572,597]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 24" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1725,1748]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1701]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 24. Habitus of Polycaena taxa at same scale. 1 – 8 — Polycaena kansuensis; 1 – 2 — syntype ♂ and its labels; 3 – 6 — ♂♂ from Xiahe, S Gansu; 7 – 8 — ♂ from Xining, NE Qinghai. 9 – 13 — P. lama; 9 — syntype ♂ (after Leech [1893]); 10 — syntype ♀ (after Leech [1893]); 11 — ♂ from Litang; 12 — ♀ from Kangding; 13 — ♂ from Yajiang. 14 — P. wangjiaqii, holotype ♂. 15 – 18 — P. sejila; 15 – 16 — holotype ♂; 17 – 18 — paratype ♂. 19 – 20 — P. lua taibaiensis, ♂♂ from Chang-an, Shaanxi. 21 – 22 — P. lua lua; 21 — ♂ from Huangyuan, NE Qinghai; 22 — ♂ from Guoluo, Qinghai. 23 – 24 — P. m i no r; 23 — ♂ from Batang, W Sichuan; 24 — ♂ from Yushu, SE Qinghai. 1, 3, 5, 7, 15, 17 — upper side; 2, 4, 6, 8, 16, 18 — underside; 9 – 14, 19 – 24 — upper side (left half) and underside (right half)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258395/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">
Fig. 
<number box="[421,452,572,596]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). Both wings on upper side with all markings placed as in 
<emphasis box="[1147,1231,572,596]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">P. l a m a</emphasis>
, but colored in a different way: cell spot and postdiscal spots in spaces 
<number box="[755,765,607,632]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" value="1.0">1</number>
b- 
<number box="[792,806,607,632]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" value="5.0">5</number>
of forewing reddish orange, postdiscal spots in spaces 
<number box="[1422,1436,607,632]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" value="6.0">6</number>
and 
<number box="[198,226,644,668]" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" value="10.0">10</number>
of forewing cream, not white as in 
<emphasis box="[625,705,644,668]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">P. l ama</emphasis>
. Both wings underside exactly as in 
<taxonomicName box="[1121,1204,644,668]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Polycaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lama">
<emphasis box="[1121,1204,644,668]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="584">P. lama</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
